#Write a program that adds the digits in a 2 digit number. e.g. if the input was 35, then the output should be 3 + 5 = 8




#Request user to enter two digits
two_digit_number = input("Type a two digit number: ")



# Lets first check the data type entered.
print(type(two_digit_number))
# Tells us that this is a string data



# Select the first digit(position 0) of data entered. Lets name this as FirstDigit.
FirstDigit=two_digit_number[0]
# Printing onscreen to check
print("First Digit is: ")
print(FirstDigit)

#Select the second digit(position 1) of data entered. Lets name this as SecondDigit.
print("Second Digit is: ")
SecondDigit=two_digit_number[1]
# Printing onscreen to check
print(SecondDigit)



#Converts both string data to integer data so that we can perform math operation(adding).
Result = int(FirstDigit) + int(SecondDigit)

# Prints out result
print("Sum of First Digit and Second Digit: ")
print(Result)
